name: Barcelona vs PSG
summary: The highly anticipated Champions League match between Barcelona and Paris Saint-Germain took place on April 16, 2024. The game, live-streamed globally, saw PSG emerge victorious with a 4-1 scoreline, eliminating Barcelona from the competition. Kylian Mbappe was the star of the match, scoring a late brace to secure the win. The match was marked by controversy, with Barcelona's Ronald Araujo and manager Xavi Hernandez receiving red cards. Despite a valiant effort and an early goal from Raphinha, Barcelona's hopes of a comeback were dashed by PSG's dominance in the second half. The result leaves PSG advancing to the next round of the Champions League, while Barcelona's European campaign comes to an end.
